    <title>Manage favorites</title>
    <para>Saving your charts as favorites makes it easy to find them later. You can also choose to
        share them with other users as an interpretation or display them on the dashboard.</para>
    <para>You can view the details and interpretations of your favorites when you open the
            <?oxy_comment_start author="rachaelb" timestamp="20161010T224006+0200" comment="For 2.26 favorites will be also applied to: event reports, event visualizer, GIS"?><emphasis
            role="bold">Pivot table</emphasis> or <emphasis role="bold">Data
            Visualization</emphasis> app<?oxy_comment_end?>. You can edit descriptions, share your
        favorites, or write interpretations directly in this pane, or you can use the <emphasis
            role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> menu.</para>
    <section>
        <title>Open a favorite</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                        >Open</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Search for favorites by entering the name of the favorite in the search field,
                    or use <emphasis role="bold">Prev</emphasis> and <emphasis role="bold"
                        >Next</emphasis> to display favorites.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Save a favorite</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Save
                        as</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Enter a name, title and description for your favorite.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title><?oxy_comment_start author="Home" timestamp="20160412T140454+0200" comment="Revise title."?>Overwrite<?oxy_comment_end?>
            a favorite</title>
        <para>To save the current chart to an existing favorite (overwrite):</para>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis>.</para>
                <para>The <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> dialog box opens.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Find the favorite you want to overwrite.</para>
                <para>You can either use <emphasis role="bold">Prev</emphasis> and <emphasis
                        role="bold">Next</emphasis> or the search field to find a saved favorite.
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><?oxy_comment_start author="rachaelb" timestamp="20161010T230638+0200" comment="Is this still applicable in 2.25?"?>Click
                    the green overwrite icon next to the favorite's name.</para>
            </listitem>
            <?oxy_comment_end?>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">OK</emphasis> to confirm that you want to
                    overwrite the favorite.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Rename a favorite</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                        >Rename</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Enter the new name for your favorite.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Update</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Write an interpretation for a favorite</title>
        <para role="">An interpretation is a link to a resource with a description of the data. You
            need to save a favorite to create an interpretation. You can share this information with
            other people.</para>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Write
                        interpretation</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><?oxy_comment_start author="rachaelb" timestamp="20161010T224321+0200" comment="Is there a set length of characters or any other criteria such as support /non-support of certain characters etc?"?>In
                    the text field, type a comment, question or interpretation.<?oxy_comment_end?>
                    You can see this information on the <emphasis role="bold"
                    >dashboard</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Add a user group that you want to share your favorite with by clicking the
                        <emphasis role="bold">+</emphasis> icon.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><?oxy_comment_start author="rachaelb" timestamp="20161010T225040+0200" comment="Check what the workflow is here with Jan Helge"?>Select:<?oxy_comment_end?><orderedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para><emphasis role="bold"
                                    ><?oxy_comment_start author="rachaelb" timestamp="20161010T154603+0200" comment="Continue updating text here based on recent UI"?>Allow
                                    external access</emphasis> if you want everyone to view this
                                interpretation.<?oxy_comment_end?></para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para><emphasis role="bold">Public access</emphasis></para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para><emphasis role="bold">Administrators</emphasis></para>
                        </listitem>
                    </orderedlist></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Share</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Create a link to a favorite</title>
        <para>
            <orderedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                            >Get link</emphasis>.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Choose one of the following:</para>
                    <itemizedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para><emphasis role="bold">Open in this app</emphasis>: You get a URL
                                for the favorite which you can share with other users by email or
                                chat.</para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para><emphasis role="bold">Open in web api</emphasis>: You get a URL of
                                the API resource. By default this is an HTML resource, but you can
                                change the file extension to &quot;.json&quot; or
                                &quot;.csv&quot;.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
        </para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Delete a favorite</title>
        <para>
            <orderedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para><?oxy_comment_start author="rachaelb" timestamp="20161010T225737+0200" comment="Does this only apply to a favorite in one app? Can favorites be shared across apps? If yes, does this have an effect if you delete a favorite in one place? 

This behavior does not exist yet - add an enhancement issue for this request"?>Click
                            <emphasis role="bold">Favorites</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                            >Delete</emphasis><?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">OK</emphasis>.</para>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
        </para>
    </section>
    <section xml:id="favorite_interpret_rel_period">
        <title>View interpretations based on relative periods</title>
        <para>To view interpretations for relative periods, such as a year ago:</para>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Open a favorite with interpretations.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">&lt;&lt;&lt;</emphasis> in the top right of the
                    workspace to view, edit, rate and comment on interpretations.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click an interpretation. The
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="rachaelb" timestamp="20161012T114005+0200" comment="update as more apps are added in 2.26"?>chart
                    or pivot table<?oxy_comment_end?> displays information based on when the
                    interpretation was created. The date of the chart or table is visible next to
                    the chart or table name, at the top of the workspace.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Comment</emphasis> to write an interpretation, and
                        <emphasis role="bold">Post</emphasis> to publish your comment on the
                    dashboard. This information will be shared with people who have saved this
                    interpretation as a favorite.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
        <para>To clear the interpretation data and display a chart or table with the most recent
            information, click <emphasis role="bold">Clear interpretation</emphasis>.</para>
        <screenshot>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata width="100%" align="center"
                        fileref="resources/images/generic/favorites_panel.png" format="PNG"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </screenshot>
    </section>
